  array('newsletter_ID' => '96','title' => 'Global Insights: Tech, Geopolitics, Health','content' => '<p>This edition of our newsletter brings you a diverse look at recent global events, from significant shifts in venture capital and private equity to pressing geopolitical incidents and public health concerns impacting communities worldwide.</p><br><h2>Private Markets: Q3 2025 Trends</h2><p>PitchBook\'s latest reports offer deep dives into the private markets, highlighting key trends in Q3 2025. The "Q3 2025 AI VC Trends" report provides crucial insights into the evolving landscape of Artificial Intelligence venture capital. Additionally, the "Q3 2025 US Public PE and GP Deal Roundup" sheds light on significant deal activities in public private equity and general partnerships across the United States. Looking ahead, the "Q4 2025 PitchBook Analyst Note: Global VC Ecosystem Rankings" will soon reveal the leading players and regions shaping the global venture capital scene. These reports are essential for understanding the dynamics of private investments.</p><br><h2>Missile Strike in Southern Russia</h2><p>A recent incident in Southern Russia saw a missile striking residential buildings in Gelendzhik on November 24, 2025. Footage captured by bystanders showed a single missile impacting a multi-story apartment block, followed by a fire. Residents were heard shouting as they recorded the events from nearby streets and balconies, amid what was described as chaotic air defense fire. This event underscores ongoing regional tensions.</p><br><h2>Leptospirosis Outbreak in Jamaica</h2><p>Jamaica is currently grappling with an outbreak of leptospirosis, which has tragically claimed six lives. Dr. Christopher Tufton, the Minister of Health and Wellness, announced the situation on November 21, 2025, during a press briefing. This outbreak comes in the aftermath of Hurricane Melissa, suggesting a potential link between the natural disaster and the rise in cases, emphasizing the vulnerability of public health systems following environmental disruptions.</p><br><p>From the complex world of private market investments and technological advancements to the stark realities of geopolitical conflicts and public health emergencies, recent global events remind us of the interconnectedness of our world. Staying informed on these diverse fronts remains crucial for understanding the challenges and opportunities that lie ahead.</p><br><h3>References:</h3><p><a href="https://pitchbook.com/news/reports/q3-2025-ai-vc-trends" target="_blank">https://pitchbook.com/news/reports/q3-2025-ai-vc-trends</a><br><a href="https://united24media.com/latest-news/missile-hit-residential-buildings-in-southern-russia-amid-chaotic-air-defense-fire-video-13741" target="_blank">https://united24media.com/latest-news/missile-hit-residential-buildings-in-southern-russia-amid-chaotic-air-defense-fire-video-13741</a><br><a href="https://www.jamaicaobserver.com/2025/11/21/six-dead-jamaica-experiences-outbreak-leptospirosis-tufton/" target="_blank">https://www.jamaicaobserver.com/2025/11/21/six-dead-jamaica-experiences-outbreak-leptospirosis-tufton/</a><br><a href="https://pitchbook.com/news/reports/q3-2025-us-public-pe-and-gp-deal-roundup" target="_blank">https://pitchbook.com/news/reports/q3-2025-us-public-pe-and-gp-deal-roundup</a><br><a href="https://pitchbook.com/news/reports/q4-2025-pitchbook-analyst-note-global-vc-ecosystem-rankings" target="_blank">https://pitchbook.com/news/reports/q4-2025-pitchbook-analyst-note-global-vc-ecosystem-rankings</a></p>','status' => 'published','creation_date' => '2025-11-27','user_ID' => '19'),
  array('newsletter_ID' => '97','title' => 'AI: Quadrupling Entrepreneurial Revenue','content' => '<p>In today\'s fast-paced business landscape, artificial intelligence (AI) is no longer just a futuristic concept; it\'s a powerful tool enabling entrepreneurs to achieve unprecedented growth and significantly boost their revenue. This newsletter explores how AI-powered strategies are helping businesses not just grow, but quadruple their earnings, setting new benchmarks for success.</p><br><h2>The New Era of Explosive Growth</h2><p>AI-driven startups are redefining growth metrics. What was once considered exceptional "T2D3" growth (triple, double, triple over five years) for SaaS companies has been superseded by "Q2T3" (quadruple, quadruple, triple, triple, triple) for successful AI ventures. "Supernova" companies are emerging, hitting approximately $40 million in Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR) in their first year and an astonishing $125 million in their second, showcasing AI\'s incredible scalability potential. This rapid expansion is also reflected in revenue multiples, where LLM vendors command an impressive 44.1x compared to traditional software\'s 12x.</p><br><h2>Diverse AI-Powered Revenue Streams</h2><p>Entrepreneurs are leveraging AI to unlock various lucrative revenue models. AI-as-a-Service (AIaaS) offers recurring income through API access and usage-based pricing, a model successfully demonstrated by companies like OpenAI. Monetizing proprietary datasets through data licensing creates competitive advantages and consistent income streams. Furthermore, developing vertical AI solutions—industry-specific applications that solve pain points in sectors like healthcare or finance—allows businesses to target niche markets with highly valued offerings. Hybrid models, combining subscriptions, usage fees, and professional services, also offer robust revenue generation. This leads to remarkable efficiency; AI Supernovas achieve an average of $1.13 million ARR per full-time employee, significantly outperforming typical SaaS benchmarks.</p><br><h2>Personalization and Agentic AI for Exponential Returns</h2><p>AI\'s ability to drive hyper-personalization is a game-changer for revenue. Companies that deliver personalized customer experiences grow 2.5 times faster. Startups using AI for personalization report 1.7 times higher revenue growth and up to 50% lower customer acquisition costs. Real-world examples show AI-powered recommendation engines contributing up to 35% of total e-commerce revenue, and personalized product suggestions boosting average order value by 20-50%. Dynamic pricing strategies powered by AI can further increase revenue by 25%. Beyond personalization, agentic AI systems create a multiplier effect. They can handle increased customer interactions without additional headcount, allowing businesses to scale revenue faster than expenses while continuously learning and adapting based on feedback loops.</p><br><p>The integration of AI into entrepreneurial strategies is a clear pathway to not just incremental gains, but exponential revenue growth. From unprecedented scalability and diverse income models to hyper-personalized customer experiences and efficient operations, AI offers entrepreneurs the tools to revolutionize their businesses and achieve remarkable financial success.</p><br><h3>References:</h3><p><a href="https://www.secondtalent.com/resources/key-success-factors-for-ai-startups/" target="_blank">https://www.secondtalent.com/resources/key-success-factors-for-ai-startups/</a><br><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/rayzinn_legal-ai-startup-harvey-hits-100-million-activity-7361178976700022784-VGM-" target="_blank">https://www.linkedin.com/posts/rayzinn_legal-ai-startup-harvey-hits-100-million-activity-7361178976700022784-VGM-</a><br><a href="https://beam.ai/agentic-insights/what-is-agentic-ai-why-every-entrepreneur-should-care-in-2025" target="_blank">https://beam.ai/agentic-insights/what-is-agentic-ai-why-every-entrepreneur-should-care-in-2025</a><br><a href="https://www.bvp.com/atlas/the-state-of-ai-2025" target="_blank">https://www.bvp.com/atlas/the-state-of-ai-2025</a><br><a href="https://maccelerator.la/en/blog/entrepreneurship/ai-powered-customer-personalization-case-studies-from-successful-startups/" target="_blank">https://maccelerator.la/en/blog/entrepreneurship/ai-powered-customer-personalization-case-studies-from-successful-startups/</a></p>','status' => 'published','creation_date' => '2025-11-27','user_ID' => '19'),
  array('newsletter_ID' => '98','title' => 'Watermelon: A Sweet Debate','content' => '<p>Watermelon often sparks discussion regarding its health profile. While some might label it as "unhealthy," a closer look reveals a fruit packed with beneficial properties, alongside a few considerations. Let\'s slice into the facts to understand both the pros and cons of this popular summer treat.</p><br><h2>The Refreshing Upsides</h2><p>Beyond its delicious taste, watermelon is a hydrating powerhouse, composed of over 90% water. This makes it an excellent choice for staying refreshed, especially in warmer weather. It\'s also a good source of essential nutrients, including Vitamin C and powerful antioxidants like lycopene, which contribute to overall well-being. Furthermore, research suggests that watermelon may aid in digestion and some studies even point to potential benefits for individuals with metabolic syndrome.</p><br><h2>Potential Pitfalls to Consider</h2><p>Despite its many advantages, watermelon isn\'t without its considerations. One common concern is its relatively high sugar content. While natural, consuming large quantities can lead to blood sugar spikes, which is particularly relevant for individuals managing blood glucose levels, including pregnant women. For some, watermelon\'s high FODMAP content can trigger digestive discomfort. It\'s also important to note that relying solely on watermelon as part of a "watermelon diet" can lead to nutritional deficiencies, as it lacks protein and other vital nutrients necessary for a balanced diet.</p><br><h2>Enjoying Watermelon Mindfully</h2><p>The key to enjoying watermelon as part of a healthy lifestyle lies in moderation and balance. Integrating it into a varied diet ensures you reap its benefits without overdoing the sugar. Be mindful of your body\'s individual response, especially if you have sensitivities to FODMAPs or are monitoring blood sugar. When consumed thoughtfully, watermelon can be a delightful and nutritious addition to your plate.</p><br><p>In conclusion, watermelon is far from being inherently "unhealthy." It offers significant hydration and a good array of vitamins and antioxidants. By understanding its potential drawbacks and consuming it in moderation as part of a balanced diet, you can enjoy all the sweet benefits this vibrant fruit has to offer.</p><br><h3>References:</h3><p><a href="https://smart.dhgate.com/is-watermelon-bad-for-you-side-effects-potential-downsides/" target="_blank">https://smart.dhgate.com/is-watermelon-bad-for-you-side-effects-potential-downsides/</a><br><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266886" target="_blank">https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266886</a><br><a href="https://www.cozymeal.com/magazine/is-watermelon-healthy" target="_blank">https://www.cozymeal.com/magazine/is-watermelon-healthy</a><br><a href="https://www.vinmec.com/eng/blog/eating-watermelon-during-pregnancy-benefits-and-disadvantages-en" target="_blank">https://www.vinmec.com/eng/blog/eating-watermelon-during-pregnancy-benefits-and-disadvantages-en</a><br><a href="https://www.seasonhealth.com/blog/what-is-the-watermelon-diet-benefits-and-risks" target="_blank">https://www.seasonhealth.com/blog/what-is-the-watermelon-diet-benefits-and-risks</a></p>','status' => 'published','creation_date' => '2025-11-27','user_ID' => '20'),
  array('newsletter_ID' => '99','title' => 'Baszucki’s Baffling Interview Performance','content' => '<p>In a recent appearance on The New York Times\' "Hard Fork" podcast, Roblox CEO David Baszucki offered a truly bewildering display, managing to turn what should have been a serious discussion into a masterclass of evasion and questionable rhetoric. Those hoping for clear answers on critical issues were undoubtedly left scratching their heads, if not outright appalled, by his seemingly tone-deaf responses and agitated demeanor. It appears the spotlight of scrutiny proved far too intense for the platform’s leading figure, revealing a concerning detachment from the realities of its user base.</p><br><h2>Predators: A Lucrative "Opportunity"?</h2><p>Perhaps the most striking moment of the interview came when Baszucki addressed the persistent "problem of predators on Roblox." Rather than acknowledging a serious threat, he astoundingly reframed it, suggesting it was "not necessarily just as a problem, but an opportunity as well." One can only marvel at such a unique perspective, where safeguarding vulnerable users is apparently secondary to "building the future of communication." It seems the company\'s priorities lie in exploring abstract concepts rather than confronting tangible dangers.</p><br><h2>The CEO’s Defensive Dance</h2><p>As the conversation delved deeper into the uncomfortable territory of child safety, Baszucki’s composure visibly unraveled. Described as "flustered" and engaging in a "high-strung back-and-forth," he seemingly struggled to maintain a coherent stance. He even resorted to accusing his interviewers of "aligning" with Roblox\'s decisions and "stealthily support[ing] it," a truly bizarre deflection for someone supposedly confident in their company\'s approach. His declared "excitement to talk" felt less like genuine enthusiasm and more like a desperate attempt to steer the discussion away from inconvenient truths.</p><br><h2>AI Gating: A Convenient Distraction?</h2><p>While the interview nominally centered on Roblox\'s new AI-powered age-gating technology, Baszucki appeared remarkably unwilling to dwell on it, or indeed, any aspect of safety, for too long. He seemingly tired of the topic, reportedly responding with a flippant "Fun. Let’s keep going down this" when pressed on reports of prioritizing growth over safety. This eagerness to move past serious concerns about user well-being, even when discussing the very features meant to address them, speaks volumes about where the company’s true focus lies.</p><br><p>Ultimately, Baszucki’s latest interview painted a less-than-reassuring picture. His disingenuous framing of serious safety issues as "opportunities," combined with his visibly defensive and dismissive attitude, left a strong impression of a leader uncomfortable with accountability and seemingly more interested in rhetorical acrobatics than genuinely addressing the pressing concerns of his platform.</p><br><h3>References:</h3><p><a href="https://www.pcgamer.com/games/interview-with-roblox-ceo-kicks-off-with-an-unbelievable-answer-about-its-predator-problem-being-not-just-a-problem-but-an-opportunity-and-somehow-just-gets-crazier-from-there/" target="_blank">https://www.pcgamer.com/games/interview-with-roblox-ceo-kicks-off-with-an-unbelievable-answer-about-its-predator-problem-being-not-just-a-problem-but-an-opportunity-and-somehow-just-gets-crazier-from-there/</a><br><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/roblox-ceo-responds-to-child-predator-concerns-poorly/" target="_blank">https://www.gamespot.com/articles/roblox-ceo-responds-to-child-predator-concerns-poorly/</a><br><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2025/11/23/roblox-ceo-interview-gets-heated-over-child-safety/" target="_blank">https://techcrunch.com/2025/11/23/roblox-ceo-interview-gets-heated-over-child-safety/</a><br><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/21/podcasts/hardfork-roblox-child-safety.html" target="_blank">https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/21/podcasts/hardfork-roblox-child-safety.html</a></p>','status' => 'published','creation_date' => '2025-11-27','user_ID' => '21'),
  array('newsletter_ID' => '100','title' => 'Urban Raccoons: Evolving Domestication?','content' => '<p>Often affectionately dubbed "trash pandas," city-dwelling raccoons are more than just clever scavengers. Recent scientific studies suggest these masked mammals are showing early, fascinating signs of domestication, evolving alongside human environments in unexpected ways.</p><br><h2>The Mark of Domestication: Shorter Snouts</h2><p>A landmark study published in the journal *Frontiers in Zoology* reveals a compelling physical change in urban raccoons: shorter snouts compared to their rural counterparts. This isn\'t just a cosmetic shift; it\'s a key indicator of "domestication syndrome," a collection of traits observed in many domesticated animals. Shorter snouts are often linked to a more "juvenile" or "cute" appearance, which can foster tolerance and closer interaction with humans. This physical adaptation highlights how profoundly their urban lifestyle is influencing their evolutionary trajectory.</p><br><h2>Domestication\'s Unexpected Start</h2><p>Traditionally, domestication was thought to be a process initiated primarily by humans through selective breeding. However, the new research proposes a different beginning: animals adapting to human-created environments. For raccoons, this journey likely began with their astute ability to scavenge for food in urban rubbish bins. This constant interaction and reliance on human-adjacent resources may be the catalyst, gradually habituating them to human presence and setting them on a path towards domestication, even without direct human intervention in their breeding.</p><br><h2>Coexistence and Future Trajectories</h2><p>While the concept of domesticated raccoons might evoke images of new household pets, experts caution that these are early signs. Raccoons, for instance, currently lack the specific social structures characteristic of truly domesticated animals like dogs. Nevertheless, their increasing comfort and prevalence in urban areas have practical implications, such as the New York City Health Department\'s ongoing efforts to vaccinate raccoons against rabies to protect both residents and their pets. This ongoing coexistence underscores a unique evolutionary experiment, revealing how wildlife continues to adapt and change in our rapidly urbanizing world.</p><br><p>The evolving "trash panda" offers a compelling case study into the subtle yet significant ways animals are responding to human presence. The journey of urban raccoons provides a fascinating glimpse into the very beginnings of a process that could, over millennia, lead to profound changes in species living alongside us.</p><br><h3>References:</h3><p><a href="https://nypost.com/2025/11/21/science/raccoons-are-evolving-to-be-as-cute-and-cuddly-as-pets-study/" target="_blank">https://nypost.com/2025/11/21/science/raccoons-are-evolving-to-be-as-cute-and-cuddly-as-pets-study/</a><br><a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c1j8j48e5z2o" target="_blank">https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c1j8j48e5z2o</a><br><a href="https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/urban-raccoons-are-showing-signs-of-early-domestication-with-shorter-snouts-than-their-rural-cousins-180987729/" target="_blank">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/urban-raccoons-are-showing-signs-of-early-domestication-with-shorter-snouts-than-their-rural-cousins-180987729/</a><br><a href="https://www.cnn.com/2025/11/24/science/raccoons-urban-trash-domestication-shorter-snouts" target="_blank">https://www.cnn.com/2025/11/24/science/raccoons-urban-trash-domestication-shorter-snouts</a></p>','status' => 'published','creation_date' => '2025-11-27','user_ID' => '20'),
  array('newsletter_ID' => '101','title' => '6-7: Humanity\'s Peak Meme','content' => '<p>Prepare yourselves, for a new era of comedic genius has dawned, heralded by the enigmatic phrase "6-7." This seemingly simple utterance, championed by the brilliant minds of Generation Alpha, is not just a meme; it is the pinnacle of human humor, a testament to our species\' comedic evolution. Forget slapstick, satire, or wordplay – the pure, unadulterated absurdity of "6-7" signifies that humanity, with Gen Alpha at the helm, has officially peaked.</p><br><h2>The Mystic Numbers: Unpacking "6-7"</h2><p>Originating on TikTok and Instagram Reels in 2025, "6-7" (or "six seven," 67, 6 7, 6, 7) rapidly transcended its humble beginnings to become Gen Alpha\'s signature phrase. While some might trace its roots to the rhythmic repetitions in Skrilla\'s "Doot Doot (6 7)" song, its true power lies in its delightful inscrutability. As one astute observer noted, "6-7" is an inside joke that grows funnier with every adult who grapples, and inevitably fails, to comprehend its profound meaning. It\'s a linguistic wink, a cultural shibboleth that beautifully encapsulates the generational divide and the evolving landscape of online humor.</p><br><h2>Gen Alpha: The Architects of Absurdity</h2><p>Generation Alpha, born into a world of digital native fluency, has mastered a form of humor that bypasses traditional comedic structures. Their genius lies in finding humor in the abstract, the non-sequitur, and the shared understanding of an inside joke. "6-7" isn\'t funny because of a punchline; it\'s funny because it simply *is*. This generation thrives on self-referential humor and the joy of shared, often nonsensical, cultural touchstones. Their ability to elevate a seemingly random number combination into a global phenomenon demonstrates a sophisticated understanding of virality and the power of collective, unadorned amusement.</p><br><h2>Why "6-7" Reigns Supreme in Comedy</h2><p>The comedic brilliance of "6-7" lies precisely in its lack of conventional explanation. It defies analysis, mocking those who seek a deeper meaning where none is explicitly intended. This is comedy at its most distilled: pure, unadulterated absurdity. It\'s a rejection of old comedic paradigms, embracing a form that prioritizes shared experience and the joy of collective bewilderment. In an increasingly complex world, "6-7" offers a refreshing, almost Zen-like, simplicity that is both hilarious and profoundly indicative of a species that has reached its comedic zenith. We have, indeed, peaked, and the numbers "6-7" are our glorious, nonsensical monument.</p><br><p>From its mysterious origins to its widespread adoption by Generation Alpha, "6-7" stands as a monumental achievement in human humor. It challenges us to rethink what makes something funny, proving that sometimes, the most profound comedy comes from the most unexpected, and unexplained, places. Gen Alpha\'s embrace of "6-7" is a clear signal: the future of humor is wonderfully absurd, brilliantly incomprehensible, and utterly, unequivocally hilarious.</p><br><h3>References:</h3><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/philstarlife/posts/gen-alphas-6-7-explainedit-started-as-a-meme-became-a-trend-and-now-6-7-is-gen-a/1260611576084433/" target="_blank">https://www.facebook.com/philstarlife/posts/gen-alphas-6-7-explainedit-started-as-a-meme-became-a-trend-and-now-6-7-is-gen-a/1260611576084433/</a><br><a href="https://www.instagram.com/reel/DSCrTJygZ2h/" target="_blank">https://www.instagram.com/reel/DSCrTJygZ2h/</a><br><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/6-7_(meme)" target="_blank">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/6-7_(meme)</a><br><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/07/style/gen-z-six-seven-meme-gen-alpha-absurdity.html" target="_blank">https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/07/style/gen-z-six-seven-meme-gen-alpha-absurdity.html</a><br><a href="https://people.com/what-does-six-seven-mean-all-about-tiktok-trend-11724247" target="_blank">https://people.com/what-does-six-seven-mean-all-about-tiktok-trend-11724247</a></p>','status' => 'published','creation_date' => '2025-12-09','user_ID' => '20'),
  array('newsletter_ID' => '102','title' => 'Raccoon Revelation: Not Domestication','content' => '<p>We sincerely apologize for an inaccuracy in our previous newsletter regarding raccoon behavior. We understand the importance of providing correct information, and we deeply regret any misunderstanding caused by our earlier statement suggesting that raccoons were naturally becoming domesticated. We are committed to upholding the highest standards of accuracy, and we assure you that such an oversight will not happen again.</p><br><h2>Debunking the Domestication Myth</h2><p>In our last edition, we discussed the fascinating adaptability of raccoons and, regrettably, misinterpreted recent observations as early signs of natural domestication. While raccoons are undeniably intelligent and resourceful, their increasing presence in urban environments and seemingly familiar interactions with humans were incorrectly attributed to a pathway towards domestication. We acknowledge that domestication is a complex process involving selective breeding over many generations, guided by human intervention, which was not the case in our previous assertion.</p><br><h2>The Subspecies Truth Emerges</h2><p>Recent research has clarified that what we were observing is not a natural domestication process, but rather the emergence of new raccoon subspecies. These distinct groups are developing due to natural evolutionary pressures and adaptation to diverse environments, including human-dominated landscapes. This is a testament to the raccoon\'s incredible ability to adapt to new niches, not a sign of them becoming pets or farm animals through an inherent evolutionary drive. The slight variations in behavior, diet, and physical characteristics that led to our earlier misinterpretation are instead indicators of natural diversification within the species.</p><br><h2>Understanding Raccoon Evolution</h2><p>The distinction between a new subspecies and domestication is crucial. Subspecies arise when populations of a species become reproductively isolated and adapt to their specific habitats, leading to genetic and phenotypic differences. This is a natural process driven by environmental factors. Domestication, on the other hand, involves intentional human selection for desirable traits, fundamentally altering an animal\'s genetic makeup and behavior to suit human needs. Our earlier report conflated these two distinct biological phenomena, and for this, we are truly sorry.</p><br><p>We are dedicated to providing you with accurate and reliable scientific information. We have learned from this error and are implementing stricter review processes to ensure the veracity of all our content. Thank you for your understanding, and we promise to earn back your trust with meticulous reporting in future newsletters.</p><br><h3>References:</h3><p><a href="https://www.trvst.world/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/north-american-raccoon-procyon-lotor-600x461.jpg" target="_blank">https://www.trvst.world/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/north-american-raccoon-procyon-lotor-600x461.jpg</a><br><a href="https://images-wixmp-ed30a86b8c4ca887773594c2.wixmp.com/f/55f01c9f-1606-46c0-95d1-63dd96eb8ff1/di12sd2-6bd438bc-a904-4199-b79e-fec0f6a2b5df.png/v1/fill/w_1168,h_684,q_70,strp/raccoon_subspecies_by_abrarzaim_di12sd2-pre.jpg?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..O890Qyd_fysp7w0rm5iyHaMv09FEzQuMxc4nR_fcdjw" target="_blank">https://images-wixmp-ed30a86b8c4ca887773594c2.wixmp.com/f/55f01c9f-1606-46c0-95d1-63dd96eb8ff1/di12sd2-6bd438bc-a904-4199-b79e-fec0f6a2b5df.png/v1/fill/w_1168,h_684,q_70,strp/raccoon_subspecies_by_abrarzaim_di12sd2-pre.jpg?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..O890Qyd_fysp7w0rm5iyHaMv09FEzQuMxc4nR_fcdjw</a><br><a href="https://images-wixmp-ed30a86b8c4ca887773594c2.wixmp.com/f/55f01c9f-1606-46c0-95d1-63dd96eb8ff1/di26cmr-34ac95ab-e3fe-4d53-946e-5c17d29864b8.png/v1/fill/w_1280,h_519,q_80,strp/crab_eating_raccoon_subspecies_by_abrarzaim_di26cmr-fullview.jpg?token=eyJ0eXAiO